events.1510: Battle of Salt River: A Portuguese force led by Francisco de Almeida is defeated by the indigenous Goringhaiqua Khoikhoi clan.
events.1651: Jan van Riebeeck visits the Cape as part of a rescue mission to save stranded sailors.
events.1652: Jan van Riebeeck of the Dutch East India Company arrives.
events.1714: Kenridge, then known as Blommesteijn, started.
events.1757: During the Seven Years' War, a naval action takes place off the Cape of Good Hope between British and unidentified (likely French) vessels.
events.1786: Committee of the High Court established.
events.1792: The Lutheran Church in Strand Street was built.
events.1795: British in power in Cape Colony.
events.1802: Freemason's Lodge built on Bouquet Street.
events.1803: Dutch regain power in Cape Colony by the Treaty of Amiens.
events.1804: Coat of arms of Cape Town in use.
events.1806: Battle of Blaauwberg: British victory over the Batavian Republic during the Napoleonic Wars.
events.1814: Cape Town ceded to Britain by the Anglo–Dutch Treaty of 1814.
events.1829: Vagrancy and pass laws of 1809 repealed.
events.1830: Cape of Good Hope Literary Gazette begins publication.
events.1840: Michiel van Breda became the first mayor.
events.1841: Cape Town Mail newspaper begins publication.
events.1847: Anglican Diocese of Cape Town established.
events.1857: Cape Argus newspaper and Cape Monthly Magazine begin publication.
events.1872: Cape attains responsible government, led by its first Prime Minister John Molteno.
events.1873: University of the Cape of Good Hope founded.
events.1877: First South African International Exhibition is held in Cape Town.
events.1878: First telephones are set up in the Cape.
events.1885: Standard Bank of South Africa headquarters relocates to Cape Town.
events.1892: The Franchise and Ballot Act of Cecil Rhodes places restrictions on the multiracial Cape Qualified Franchise.
events.1901: St. George's Cathedral, Cape Town foundations laid.
events.1905: Cape Town City Hall and Synagogue built.
events.1910: Cape Town becomes the capital of the Union of South Africa.
events.1919: Industrial and Commercial Workers' Union founded.
events.1922: Pinelands (suburb) South Africa's first Garden City established.
events.1926: Hoërskool Jan van Riebeeck was founded.
events.1928: Table Mountain Aerial Cableway begins operating.
events.1930: South African National Gallery building opens.
events.1936: St. George's Cathedral and Table Bay power station constructed.
events.1939: Catholic Vicariate of Cape Town active.
events.1956: Maynardville Open-Air Theatre holds its first Shakespeare performance.
events.1960: Sentinel News and Contrast magazine begin publication.
events.1961: City becomes part of the Republic of South Africa.
events.1964: Rivonia Trialists imprisoned to life sentence in Robben Island.
events.1979: Monument Park High School was founded.
events.1982: Laloo Chiba was released from custody of Apartheid government.
events.1985: Desmond Tutu becomes archbishop of the Anglican Diocese of Cape Town.
events.1993: Saint James Church massacre occurs in Kenilworth.
events.1996: Cape Town/Central, Tygerberg, South Peninsula, Blaauwberg, Oostenberg, and Helderberg municipalities created.
events.2000: City of Cape Town metropolitan municipality formed.
events.2003: Cape Town International Convention Centre opens.
events.2006: Neighbourgoods Market in business in Woodstock.
events.2007: September: International meeting of educators produces Open Education Declaration.
events.2016: Cape Town City F.C. was formed.
events.2017: September: Zeitz Museum of Contemporary Art Africa to open.
events.2018: July: International Wikimania meeting held in Cape Town.
